Unholy Death Knight.note: A rather potent proc trinket, and among the best for Unholy. In single-target scenarios, it is very close between pacemaker and astral antenna, though in other scenarios it loses out to Void Touched Fragment.

Havoc Demon Hunter.note: Astral Antenna spawns little orbs that float towards you, and when collected give a buff of Critical Strike for 10 seconds. Multiple orb buffs can overlap each having their own 10 second timer. These orbs take ABOUT 6 seconds to reach you without movement, however you have 20 seconds to get them before they despawn. This trinket is BiS in all content with current tuning and the mini-game portions of it are not too involved or distracting so it is recommended.

So'leahs can be a great trinket IF you have a target to get Critical Strike or Mastery from the buff, and gives 20% value to your ally you use it on as well. A great passive option for all content and will

Sigil is simply a powerful proc with an Execute mechanic, dealing significantly more damage the lower your targets HP goes. For any raid fight with end of fight burns, this will be the best passive option.

Prism provides an insanely strong and flexible On-Use effect, however it has no stats on the base and fully relies on the damage proc and on-use. This is slightly better than  Araz's Ritual Forge in Mythic+ at optimal gameplay, however in Raid it means you have no trinket for lust on pull as well as if you die you lose all your stacks making it punishing to run. It's a usable option, but double passive trinkets may perform more consistently.

As Critical Strike is our top stat, this comes as a consistent and good passive trinket that will ALWAYS give you powerful Critical Strike on pull in raid, and can have the cooldown continue out of combat for Mythic+. The extension of the buff is capped almost instantly every time we get it as we have so many small hits and high crit chance.

Prism provides an insanely strong and flexible On-Use effect, however it has no stats on the base and fully relies on the damage proc and on-use. This is slightly better than  Araz's Ritual Forge in Mythic+ at optimal gameplay, however in Raid it means you have no trinket for lust on pull as well as if you die you lose all your stacks making it punishing to run. It's a usable option, but double passive trinkets may perform more consistently.
Empowering Crystal is beaten out by Pacemaker, however it can be better if at a higher item level and is a good passive trinket for all content.

Ticking Sack of Terror sims as BiS for single target as Aldrachi Reaver, however it in cringe to play and has large downsides while the damage scales abhorrently into AoE scenarios. A good option for PURE single target, but Fel Scarred has a better damage profile for ST and wants other trinkets as a higher priority.

Due to being from Delves, this trinket hits 710 item level at max on hero track. This is a good option for Mythic+ at its item level, It procs a large amount of Mastery for 10 seconds but the uptime is rather low. This trinket is extremely bad in raid, however it excels in Mythic+ due to every mob that dies giving a fragment. This causes you to have a much higher uptime making it viable. Once you get Mythic trinkets, this typically will no longer be competitive.
While this trinket can sim incredibly well for Mythic+ in dungeon slice or dungeon sim routes, it does horrendous in actual play and should not be run at current tuning.

Balance Druid.note: Grants baseline Intellect and a Critical Strike increase when coming in contact with the floating orb. Orbs can be kited around to prolong the initial effect and ALSO stack, like Ironfur. Potentially abuseable trinket with solid baseline value. Sims very high.

An exceptionally strong on-use trinket which gives you insane amounts of Intellect. Pair it up with your Celestial Alignment. Effect lasts 30 seconds, so technically can be used with an on-use trinket.
Quite strong equip based trinket that provides both direct damage and a stat bonus. It is worth nothing that the stat effect can stack, similar to Ironfur.

Trinket provides a large amount of Intellect when empowered, which effect can stack. It also provides additional value if low on mana and is part of the Shards of the Void set from Manaforge: Omega, greatly empowering your weapons Voidglass Shards ability.
Strong baseline Intellect trinket with a Random Secondary Stat proc effect.
Provides baseline Haste while both dealing damage and granting a stacking Intellect buff once it procs. One of your more powerful equip based options.
Nice 1.5m on use trinket that gives you mastery. Strong in lieu of Ritual Forge.
Signet grants baseline Intellect and a bonus amount of your highest secondary stat when used. Trinket gains more value when you are in the same party as others using the trinket.

Feral Druid.note: This is just by far and away the best trinket, even at Normal ilvl it's the best trinket available for Feral
This is the best passive secondary trinket, it's a lot of extra crit on a respectably high uptime.
An alternative passive scondary trinket, again it's a respectable amount of stats.
Another alternative passive secondary trinket, instead of just acting as a stat stick it just is a stat stick. It does also buff your allies though this is more placebo than a meaningful benefit
Ritual Forge is by far the best on use trinket, but you still allways want to use an on use trinket, if you don't have Forge, you can use this

Guardian Druid.note: Essentially a Critical Strike stat stick. Given that we generally don't have that much Critical Strike, this is a great trinket to boost that stat up.
One of the better Tanking trinkets from dungeons.
An interesting trinket that mostly grants us some crit with a passive damage effect, that alternates to an absorb shield on if required defensively.
Once stacked up fully, if maintained, deals impressive amounts of damage passively.
Passive damage with a fairly high variance swing.
A massive amount of Agi on-use with a small amount of secondary passively.
Passive agi with a small crit proc, very decent overall.
Huge damage hit on-use.
Grants a good amount of our highest secondary stat on-use.
A nice passive haste trinket with agi that can stack up significantly with some rng.
Better for Mythic+ than raid, deals decent passive damage.
Another passive damage trinket, deals more damage the lower the targets HP is.
An interesting trinket that performs well on longer fights where it can be aligned with CD's at integral times for a huge boost of damage.
Cheat death trinket, rather weak if you are not in peril.
Very small damage and damage reduction.
Deals a small amount of damage and procs some Mastery.
Decent Agi + secondary stat stick.
Passive damage procs are arcane which is great for us.
Pretty interesting crit trinket with a small damage effect, decent overall.
Passive damage effect, deals arcane damage which also heals us as EC.

Devastation Evoker.note: An exceptionally strong on-use trinket which favors classes that have powerful 2 minute cooldowns. Effect lasts 30 seconds, so technically can be used with an on-use trinket.
Quite strong equip based trinket that provides both direct damage and a stat bonus. It is worth nothing that the stat effect can stack.
Grants baseline Intellect and a Critical Strike increase when coming in contact with the floating orb. Orbs can be kited around to prolong the initial effect and also stack.
Provides baseline Haste while both dealing damage and granting a stacking Intellect buff once it procs. One of your more powerful equip based options.
Provides baseline Intellect with an on-use Mastery bonus. Acceptable Trinket, but there are better options.

Trinket provides a large amount of Intellect when empowered, which effect can stack. It also provides additional value if low on mana and is part of the Shards of the Void set from Manaforge: Omega, greatly empowering your weapons Voidglass Shards ability.
Strong baseline Intellect trinket with a Random Secondary Stat proc effect.
Signet grants baseline Intellect and a bonus amount of your highest secondary stat when used. Trinket gains more value when you are in the same party as others using the trinket.
Passive damage proc that scales with Mastery.
Orbs spawn on your character and damage enemies or increase your Mastery if intercepted.
Passive damage proc ramps over time.
Passive damage over time proc. If a target dies with this DoT active, you gain Versatility.

Augmentation Evoker.note: This is essentially the only Intellect on-use trinket available for casters in Season 3, and it is one of the strongest trinkets options available overall. Aim to use this with Breath of Eons cooldown windows whenever possible.

Strong passive damage proc that increases in effectiveness on low mana and has shares a set bonus with several cantrip weapons from the raid, which you will be seeking anyway as a best-in-slot weapon. You can swap specs or spam abilities like  Living Flame before a pull to start an encounter on low mana, in order to maximize the value from this trinket, although the damage gain from doing so is fairly marginal.
Well-tuned trinket with a fairly straightforward effect which favours Scalecommander over Chronowarden; quite a strong passive trinket option overall.

This is one of the few on-use stat trinkets available in Season 3, and Mastery on a 90 second cooldown actually has solid potential, especially for the recommended Chronowarden playstyle this tier which has a mix of 90- and 120-second cooldown timings. Certainly one to look out for, especially if playing Chronowarden.

A solid option as far as on-use trinkets go, and has an effect which follows your character's stat priority. The two-minute cooldown will mean this does not align as nicely with Chronowarden cooldowns as 90-second alternatives. Still aim to use this with Breath of Eons cooldown windows whenever possible.
This is a decent passive trinket option newly available in Season 3, providing direct damage and Intellect along with passive Haste.

A surprisingly solid on-use trinket coming out of Delves in Season 3, although this will be more effective when played on Scalecommander than Chronowarden due to the cooldown and lowest secondary stat effect.
This is a fairly traditional stat stick providing passive Intellect and random secondary stats. The effect more highly favours Scalecommander's stat priority than Chronowarden.

Another relatively traditional stat stick, but with a twist that allows you to select the secondary stat and provide an ally with an additional benefit. The flexibility and additional value provided make this a strong option.
A crowd-favourite trinket option from Season 1, providing solid damage and Intellect through its effect. A decent passive option overall.
Passive Intellect and the effect deals direct damage to enemies. This trinket is in a decent place overall tuning-wise but is otherwise fairly unremarkable.

This trinket spawns orbs which will slowly be drawn toward you, and there is potential to outplay this trinket by kiting the orbs until you're ready with cooldowns available. That said, when it comes to Augmentation and Mastery, I wouldn't expect playing around this effect to especially worthwhile.

One of the less remarkable trinket options available from the raid in Season 3. The damaging effect has some scaling with target count and player Mastery, but neither of these factors significantly improve the value of this trinket in practice.
High potential to be strong in Mythic+ as it seems this procs on all enemy deaths and not just your own last-hits.

The 90-second cooldown of this trinket makes it more interesting this season given Chronowarden's timings, but the Versatility effect has always been somewhat underwhelming for personal throughput. In Season 1, this trinket also buffed pets in your group, reducing its overall value. That said, this is not a terrible option for Augmentation as an on-use effect to pair with cooldowns, just note that its true value will not be reflected in damage meters or logs.
A fairly unremarkable trinket with a damage-over-time effect. The additional conditional effect is inherently unreliable and Versatility is not a particularly attractive stat for any build.
Poorly tuned damaging effect, and passive Haste is not ideal.
Fairly standard trinket with passive Intellect and damaging proc obtained from Delves, not particularly remarkable.
An amusing trinket that can actually deal reasonable damage, but having to go around and kick the footbombs is entirely impractical for any reasonably challenging form of group content.
While the 90-second cooldown is interesting, this trinket remains undertuned, and having to stand in a circle for the duration is a complete non-starter is challenging group content.
Poorly tuned damaging effect, and passive Haste is not ideal. The additional target scaling does not provide enough value to be particularly relevant.

Somewhat underwhelming as far as end-boss raid trinkets go, but on the surface the output of this trinket is nothing special. The intended use of this trinket is also somewhat confusing, as the former effect encourages longer Raid encounters, while the latter effect seems more geared for shorter AoE encounters more suited for Mythic+. Overall this trinket likely needs some more buffs to see play.

This might be a reasonable trinket option for solo play, but the passive Mastery is not especially ideal for that purpose. The positional requirement and lower end damage tuning makes this difficult to recommend for group play.
This is simply not a valuable trinket for damage throughput, but can of course be considered a reasonble option for casual solo play given the additional self-healing that it provides.

Beast Mastery Hunter.note: Great passive buff that gives a lot of stats. You do not need to manage the buff or orbs for this to be BIS.
A good amount of haste and a minor source of damage on a priority taget.
A large amount of Critical Strike every minute.
A lot of random secondary stats, not much else to say.
Does a bit less for the Hunter than most of the above but the small buff to an ally makes it equivalent from a group perspective. Buff an ally that wants Haste.
The strongest option if you're playing Dark Ranger, or if you want strong burst for whatever reason.
Generally not worth the trouble of managing the stacks.

Marksmanship Hunter.note: Very strong passive, as Crit is our best stat. It is also very powerfully tuned.
Our best trinket by a mile. Macro to  Trueshot and have fun.
Only good for pure single-target as an alternative to the Antenna.

Fire Mage.note: Quite strong equip based trinket that provides both direct damage and a stat bonus. It is worth nothing that the stat effect can stack.

Trinket provides a large amount of Intellect when empowered, which effect can stack. It also provides additional value if low on mana and is part of the Shards of the Void set from Manaforge: Omega, greatly empowering your weapons Voidglass Shards ability.
Provides baseline Haste while both dealing damage and granting a stacking Intellect buff once it procs. One of your more powerful equip based options.
Grants baseline Intellect and a Critical Strike increase when coming in contact with the floating orb. Orbs can be kited around to prolong the initial effect and also stack.
Provides baseline Intellect with an on-use Mastery bonus. Acceptable Trinket, but there are better options.
Signet grants baseline Intellect and a bonus amount of your highest secondary stat when used. Trinket gains more value when you are in the same party as others using the trinket.
Strong baseline Intellect trinket with a Random Secondary Stat proc effect.
An exceptionally strong on-use trinket which favors classes that have powerful 2 minute cooldowns. Effect lasts 30 seconds, so technically can be used with an on-use trinket.
Haste trinket with a damage proc.

Brewmaster Monk.note: This tank-exclusive trinket offers a rare win of combining reliable defense with a surprising amount of damage, all while remaining passive. While it does take up to 4 minutes of combat to reach all 15 stacks of  Infuriated, these stacks decay fairly slowly when you exit it, at a rate of only one stack every 3 seconds. So long as you aren't forced to stay out of combat for extended periods of time, this trinket proves to be useful even in a mythic+ environment, and it is absolutely your best choice overall for the season. Seek it out immediately.

Making a triumphant return from Shadowlands, this trinket provides an astonishing amount of damage to make up for having Mastery as its passive stat. However, its value quickly drops off outside of single-target fighting due to the difficulty of having a target reach 3 stacks of the debuff or live long enough to see it time out to trigger a detonation. In addition, this trinket is a rare exception to the usual penalty on raw damage effects given to tank specializations, greatly inflating its value. Should this be addressed, expect it to become acceptably strong, but no longer a powerhouse of an item.

This trinket may be an effectively "boring", passive source of Critical Strike, but its generous 2.5 procs per minute of the buff make for a compelling option at all target counts for a Brewmaster that enjoys the stat.

A convenient source of passive damage across target counts, this trinket offers a frequent proc rate of 2.5ppm while increasing in power as the target loses health and even echoes its damage to nearby enemies.

So long as you do not accidentally use an ability during downtime to trigger the effect, this trinket's bonus stats can be activated fairly reliably at the start of any given pull for a burst of Critical Strike that lasts for 15 seconds. In addition, your own critical hits can extend the duration by up to another 15 seconds, and Critical Strike is a stat that Brewmasters prefer to have in the first place!

Your strongest purely defensive trinket of the season, this item offers a small amount of damage and a damage-reducing absorb on a reliable one-minute cooldown. As such, it can likely be available for any given deadly mechanic on a regular basis, making it an excellent first line of defense when you need one.

Combining consistent damage with on-use Agility, this trinket can be lined up with burst windows from  Weapons of Order or a Master of Harmony's  Coalescence, and the bonus Agility can also be used defensively as an amplifier to your  Stagger.

An alternative to  Lily of the Eternal Weave, this trinket's 2-minute cooldown is better suited to Master of Harmony Brewmasters who are more likely to have a longer  Weapons of Order cooldown. Fortunately, it will provide your favorite secondary (likely Versatility or Critical Strike) while also giving a small amount of it to any other players with the same trinket equipped as well!

Protection Paladin.note: Extremely strong st and aoe trinket that ramps over time as you take damage. It has a small defensive benefit and does exceptionally high damage if it is allowed to ramp after 4mins of being in combat. Would highly reccomend in Mythic+ although you need to make sure to extend the trinket after combat in order to make use of it to its fullest capacity.
A very good on-use trinket that aligns with cooldowns. Currently is one of the highest simming trinkets.

Cheat death trinket that does a moderate amount of passive damage and a good chunk of healing based off the damage it deals. If the trinket procs from taking fatal damage, you lose both the damage and healing part of the trinket, basically make it a dead trinket. I think this trinket is decent, its not the best but its okay.
Mediocre Tank trinket that increases your armor and gives some regen on a 1min 15 cd. It also slows you :(.
Trinket that does mediocre damage, but is cool if you want to roleplay playing football and shooting footbombs at enemies. Bend it like beckham!
Doesnt give Mainstat or do anything worthwhile.

Discipline Priest.note: This trinket synergizes perfectly with Discipline's ramp playstyle by providing a massive Mastery buff in line with  Evangelism's 90 second cooldown.
Flat Haste with intellect procs from dealing damage.
Flat Mastery with an intellect proc, made stronger with the 2pc bonus to amplify shields.
Flat intellect with orbs that move to your character to provide Critical Strike.
Incredibly powerful shielding trinket for Mythic+ content, BiS for Mythic+, mediocre for raid.
Flat intellect, use the on-use to increase your secondary stats with the highest secondary of another ally.
Intellect with stacking mastery proc that ramps up by killing enemies (does not need to be a killing blow).
2min on-use trinket, works well if  Evangelism timers are more spread out but not the best ramp trinket.
Intellect with random secondary stat proc.
2min on-use trinket. Solid for ramping in raids but not BiS.
Marks an ally with a debuff that when you single-target heal them will proc an intellect bonus for you and any overheal will create a shield on them.
Intellect with a proc Mastery effect.
Vers with high healing proc effect.

Holy Priest.note: Flat intellect with orbs that move to your character to provide Critical Strike.
2min on-use trinket. Solid for using with major cooldowns in raids but not BiS.
Flat Mastery with an intellect proc. Set bonus provides a significant boost to absorbs applied.
Incredibly powerful shielding trinket for Mythic+ content, BiS for Mythic+, mediocre for raid.
Flat intellect, use the on-use to increase your secondary stats with the highest secondary of another ally.
Intellect with random secondary stat proc.
2min on-use trinket, works well when timed with major cooldowns like  Divine Hymn.
Solid on-use trinket providing a massive Mastery buff.
Vers with high healing proc effect.
Marks an ally with a debuff that when you single-target heal them will proc an intellect bonus for you and any overheal will create a shield on them.
Intellect with a proc Mastery effect.
Intellect with stacking mastery proc that ramps up by killing enemies (does not need to be a killing blow).
Flat Haste with intellect procs from dealing damage. Solid stats if you are constantly damaging but if you fail to do so it falls off very hard

Shadow Priest.note: An exceptionally strong on-use trinket which favors classes that have powerful 2 minute cooldowns. Effect lasts 30 seconds which plays well into Shadow's extremely long cooldown windows as Archon.

This is Shadow's strongest passive option in 11.2, however in order to get the maximum benefit it must also be paired with one of the set bonus weapons from the raid. There iare also some optimisations around mana and making sure you are completely out of mana at the start of a pull.
Strong baseline Intellect trinket with a Random Secondary Stat proc effect.
Provides baseline Haste while both dealing damage and granting a stacking Intellect buff once it procs. One of your more powerful equip based options.
Signet grants baseline Intellect and a bonus amount of your highest secondary stat when used. Trinket gains more value when you are in the same party as others using the trinket.
Reasonable equip based trinket, however there are better options.

One of Shadow's better options when it comes to farmable trinkets from dungeons. However, due to the strength of Ritual Forge it's hard to justify putting any other on use trinket that high on the list.

Unusually designed trinket which requires you to run into floating orbs to get value from the procs. There's some potential to optimise when you get procs by trying to avoid orbs until you have damage available but this is likely going to be too much effort for little reward.

Outlaw Rogue.note: This is another stat trinket that provides crit. The issue is that it's just worse than  Astral Antenna in a direct way. It's not bad, just replaceable with BIS.

Similar to the previous trinket, this trinket just does so much more damage than all the other damage proc trinkets that it's the go-to for us this tier. An added bonus is that this trinket doesn't seem to be good for anybody other than Rogue, so enjoy getting this easily!
Your 2nd best option for damage proc trinkets. An added bonus is that it can help reach the important Haste breakpoint.
Your 3rd best option for damage proc trinkets.
This is another stat trinket that provides crit. The issue is that it's just worse than  Astral Antenna in a direct way. It's not bad, just replaceable with BIS.
Your 4th best option for damage proc trinkets.
This trinket is fairly decent on single targets but great on multi-targets since it provides raw stats that scale much better than the damage proc trinkets do on higher target counts, especially M+.

Similar to the previous trinket, this trinket is an okay single-target trinket but excels at higher target counts. I would mainly suggest this for pushing keys, but it's a very powerful trinket for most specs, so it might be a while before you get your hands on it. You will want to use this trinket with  Vanish.
A weird damage proc trinket where you want to avoid intercepting the orb because Mastery is a terrible stat. The damage proc is decent but not worth farming for.

This trinket is okay on paper but fairly inconsistent in terms of where and what stat you get. It's an upgrade compared to some of the really bad trinkets, but I wouldn't go out of your way for this one.
This trinket is okay and it also provides bonus stats to allies. You will want to use this on somebody with Vers as their highest stat though to get it's maximum value for yourself.

This is a very average single target trinket, and very slightly above average trinket on AoE, although it does force you to play a minigame to get the damage from it. Whether that's worth the effort is up to you.

Subtlety Rogue.note: Is the strongest on-use trinket in our arsenal on any fight that lasts five minutes or longer. The on-use effect has a 20-second cooldown but will only be used every 90 seconds with  Shadow Blades, with the exception of using it during your cooldowns when the fight is about to end before your next  Shadow Blades cast. The use allows both to be put together in a macro.

This trinket has a low cooldown of 120 seconds, but we line it up with our major cooldowns, which means we only use it once every 3 minutes. This opens up the opportunity to combine it with other strong on-use trinkets. The three-minute cooldown fits well with fight lengths below 4 minutes and can make this the best option even as the only active trinket. We use it with  Shadow Blades. The trinket does damage to you on activation so make sure to not use it when on low health.

Mastery is our absolute best stat but the amount of Mastery given is low. This is likely because a lot of the stat budget of the trinket is in the main stat. The trinket is still a very good option and is the only farmable alternative to raid options. The use is fairly simple with  Shadow Blades.

This trinket is the best passive trinket from Raids and the overall best option. Critical Strike is a good stat in a season where stat drs becomes relevant. The trinket spawns orbs you need to collect so it requires some active engagement.
This trinket is the first pure damage trinket. It has a built-in execute, increasing its damage potential slightly on longer fights or fights with damage amplifiers.
This trinket is the best passive option from Mythic+. Critical Strike is our third best stat, but the trinket offers a high amount and it is not that far behind Mastery and Versatility.
Is a solid trinket where the only downside is having no control over the buff you get. This is not that bad because we like Versatility, Mastery, and Critical Strike a lot.
This trinket is good, but becomes noticeably worse with more targets. Having the effect bound to auto attacks means boss uptime is very important to get the best value.

The only crafted option. The main drawback of this trinket is the limitations of crafted gear. It is, early on, better to invest in weapons or embellishments. This gives players a long time to collect competing options.

This trinket takes a bit of housekeeping. It is ideally used on a target with Versatility or Mastery but Critical strike is still a good option. Haste should be avoided. Versatility is usually the highest stats of tanks, which means we should be able to reliably get it even in Mythic+ dungeons.
Haste is sadly not the best stat for us, but the proc chance of the trinket is high enough to still make it a solid option.

The damage of the explosion is solid but we want to ideally collect the orb for the Mastery effect. Doing so is especially important during major cooldowns. It does not matter much outside of cooldowns.
The best delve trinket this season. Mastery is our strongest Secondary stat and killing enemies is a good way to increase the proc rate.

Enhancement Shaman.note: Provides an enormous amount of primary stat, and has a perfect 2 minute cooldown to line up with  Ascendance for  Stormbringer, and every other  Doom Winds for  Totemic. Far outclasses other on-use options, and is the best trinket available.

While Critical Strike isn't typically desirable, this comes with an excellent proc rate, a high amount per proc, and the redundancy to stack if procs overlap. Nothing flashy, it just wins purely by tuning.

The passive stat stick of the season. Also has the added benefit of being able to switch which stat you bind to depending on your current gearset or hero talent.  Stormbringer wants to bind to a Haste ally, while  Totemic binds to a Mastery ally.

Coming in just under  Suspicious Energy Drink, this is also a very consistent passive proc trinket. This can highroll to outperform it, but in turn can also land at the wrong time. Still an excellent option, and has a weighting toward  Stormbringer builds.

Excellent all-rounder proc option. Since we're heavily into secondary DRs on both Haste and Mastery this season, that it procs any stat keeps it relevant. Works well for both trees to pair with an on-use trinket.

Deals extremely high direct damage, and also comes with an extra cleave component that can be played around. Gets stronger the deeper into a fight you are as well, making it a solid raid trinket. Due to how much Enhancement likes secondaries though, it's much more tailored to single target situations.

While not as powerful as the higher rated 2-minute trinket options, this still provides bulk Mastery to overlap our burst.  Stormbringer holds this to sync up with  Ascendance, while  Totemic casts it on cooldown with  Primordial Wave, overlapping every other use with  Doom Winds.

Definitely the weakest of the 2 minute on-uses available, but it's still an on-use so fills that gap if needed. The downside of applying to your lowest secondary also isn't even too bad, considering you'll be gaining one of the few stats you definitely aren't DRing.  Stormbringer uses with  Ascendance, and  Totemic with  Doom Winds.

Restoration Shaman.note: A strong stat-stick that gives us a large amount of Critical Strike. It's passive, which means it pairs nicely with pretty much any other trinket, and it's strong in both Raid and M+.

Another good stat-stick that is beneficial to both yourself and an ally of your choosing. This lets you select either the best secondary stat for yourself, your friend, or if you're lucky - you both benefit. This only lasts for 30 minutes, so you will want to have this tracked in case it falls off.

Another stat-stick that gives a good amount of Critical Strike. This does only come from delves, so getting it at a high item level is random, however if you get one early on in the season it will serve you quite well for awhile.
A fantastic 2-minute on-use trinket that gives yourself your highest secondary stat and all other party members that same stat for 20 sec. This pairs nicely with cooldowns such as  Ascendance.
Another simple stat-stick, however this increases a random secondary stat instead of a chosen one. This has relatively high uptime, making it a solid all-around trinket.
NOTE: This trinket is slightly worse until you get the set-weapon from the raid. Once you complete the set, this trinket becomes quite solid.

This is a niche trinket with a powerful on-use effect, especially in M+. Simply using it on cooldown will result in a good amount of healing, but planned uses to prevent 1-shots will be where this trinket shines.

Mastery is not a great stat, but this trinket is currently overbudget. If you happen to get it at a high item level it may perform well, but seeing as it's from delves this probably won't be a popular trinket.

A decent stat-stick with high uptime. This is nice to farm for since it's a relatively strong trinket for both Elemental and Enhance, making it a great multi-spec trinket to use if you ever swap roles.

This trinket is a powerful 2-minute on-use trinket that lines up nicely with  Ascendance, however it does have a drawback - taking away your health. Be careful using this on scary parts of encounters when there's a lot of damage happening, or in Mythic+ high keys when 1-shots become much more prevalent, as the loss of hp can kill you. If you can deal with the downsides, this trinket is very good.

Affliction Warlock.note: An exceptionally strong on-use trinket which favors classes that have powerful 2 minute cooldowns. Effect lasts 30 seconds, so technically can be used with an on-use trinket.
Quite strong equip based trinket that provides both direct damage and a stat bonus. It is worth nothing that the stat effect can stack, similar to Ironfur.

Trinket provides a large amount of Intellect when empowered, which effect can stack. It also provides additional value if low on mana and is part of the Shards of the Void set from Manaforge: Omega, greatly empowering your weapons Voidglass Shards ability.
Strong baseline Intellect trinket with a Random Secondary Stat proc effect.
Provides baseline Haste while both dealing damage and granting a stacking Intellect buff once it procs. One of your more powerful equip based options.
Signet grants baseline Intellect and a bonus amount of your highest secondary stat when used. Trinket gains more value when you are in the same party as others using the trinket.

Grants baseline Intellect and a Critical Strike increase when coming in contact with the floating orb. Orbs can be kited around to prolong the initial effect and ALSO stack, like Ironfur. Potentially abuseable trinket with solid baseline value.
Provides baseline Intellect with an on-use Mastery bonus. Acceptable Trinket, but there are better options.
